-- Brazil to Lower Import Tax for High-Tech Machines, Estado Says
-- B y   C r i s t i a n e   L u c c h e s i
-- 2012-02-05T15:13:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-05/brazil-to-lower-import-tax-for-high-tech-machines-estado-says.html
Brazil  plans to lower  import taxes 
for machinery used to produce digital TVs, personal computers,
semiconductors and other telecommunications products, O Estado
de S. Paulo  reported , citing Mauro Borges Lemos, president of
the industrial development agency that’s known as ABDI.  The tax reduction, which will apply only to machines that
aren’t produced in Brazil, aims to boost the country’s
competitiveness, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cristiane Lucchesi in  Sao Paulo  at 
 clucchesi5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at 
 swier@bloomberg.net . 